\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Test-set generalization metrics across training scales. Top: Training loss decreases monotonically (left axis), but test-set NLL exhibits a U-curve with minimum at n=4,000 (right axis). Bottom: Test perplexity (PPL) mirrors NLL, confirming n=4,000 as optimal. The n=5,000 model overfits despite achieving lowest training loss.}}{9}{figure.caption.19}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:scale_test_nll}{{6}{9}{Test-set generalization metrics across training scales. Top: Training loss decreases monotonically (left axis), but test-set NLL exhibits a U-curve with minimum at n=4,000 (right axis). Bottom: Test perplexity (PPL) mirrors NLL, confirming n=4,000 as optimal. The n=5,000 model overfits despite achieving lowest training loss}{figure.caption.19}{}}
